odia:\n\nAt a dinner given by Chou En-lai on 21 June, the Viet Minh delegate took a conciliatory line.\n\nHe \"accepted the principle\" of a Viet Minh withdrawal from Laos and Cambodia and emphasized his concern over the possibility of American bases in those states.\n\nThe Viet Minh delegate asserted that most of the Viet Minh forces in Laos have already been withdrawn. In saying this, he implied that the remainder constitutes a native \"resistance movement\" which the Communists consider a more valuable asset than the movement in Cambodia.\n\nCommunists clearly seem to be moving toward an understanding which would in effect neutralize Laos and Cambodia or at least prevent them from participating in a Southeast Asian defense organization", "token_count": 128, "token_end_0based": 127, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "2 viet minh suggests willingness to neutralize laos and cambodia at a dinner given by chou en-lai on 21 june the viet minh delegate took a conciliatory line he accepted the principle of a viet minh withdrawal from laos and cambodia and emphasized his concern over the possibility of american bases in those states the viet minh delegate asserted that most of the viet minh forces in laos have already been withdrawn in saying this he implied that the remainder constitutes a native resistance movement which the communists consider a more valuable asset than the movement in cambodia communists clearly seem to be moving toward an understanding which would in effect neutralize laos and cambodia or at least prevent them from participating in a southeast asian defense organization", "unred_source_page": 4}
